title: Bug 121170 - getColumnLabel() should return user recognizable strings
OB: When calling IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before/after data extraction, different labels are returned.
EB: The method IMetaData.getColumnLabel() should return the same labels before and after data extraction to ensure consistency for end users.
SR:
To reproduce the issue:
1. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() before data extraction.
2. Call IMetaData.getColumnLabel() after data extraction.
3. Compare the labels returned before and after to observe the inconsistency in labeling.
